cocus#Workshop: The workshop is a child of the conference.
cocus#Event: The event Thing is the child of the workshop and the conference. It is also the parent of the symposium.
cocus#User: The user is the parent of the author and the corresponding author. The user is also the child of Thing and the committee.
cocus#Role: The role of the parent of committerole is that of the child of Thing. The parent of authorrole and headrole is also the parent of adminrole.
cocus#Help_Request: helprequest is a child of request and featurerequest. It is also the parent of eventapproval and helprequest.
cocus#Person: The parent of a Thing is the user, the parent of a committee and the parent of the administrator.
cocus#Symposium: The symposium is the parent event of the workshop.
cocus#Abstract: The abstract is child of paper which is parented by invitedpaper.
cocus#Paper: The paper is the parent of invitedpaper, shortpaper and abstract. It is also the child of Thing.
cocus#Administrator: The administrator is the child of the user and the parent of the user.
cocus#Document: The parent of a document is email. It is also the parent of approval email. It is also the parent of the abstract and the submission.
cocus#Invited_Paper: invitedpaper is a child of paper which is the parent of fullpage.
cocus#Admin_Role: The role of adminrole is child of Thing.
cocus#Paper_Typologies: papertypologies is the child of eventsetup which is the parent of researchtopic.
cocus#Event_Setup: eventsetup is the parent of submissiontemplate, papertypologies, researchtopic, emailtemplate and eventtracks.
cocus#Event_URL: url is a child of url.
cocus#URL: url is the parent of eventual.
cocus#Notification_Email: notificationemail is a child of email and is parented by groupmail.
cocus#Email: Email is the child of document, review and approval. It is also the parent of notification and groupmail.
cocus#Short_Paper: The short paper is a child of paper and a document. It is also a child of a Thing.
cocus#Author_Role: The author role is the child of the head role and the parent role.
cocus#Preview: preview is a child of reviewform which is parented by reviewformsetup.
cocus#Review_Form: reviewform is a child of eventsetup which is the parent of submissiontemplate. It is also the parent of reviewformsetup and preview.
cocus#Review: Review is a child of document which is a child of Thing.
cocus#Committe_Role: Committerole is a child of Thing.
cocus#Group_Email: Groupmail is a child of email and a document. Thing is also a child of email.
cocus#Submission_Template: The submissiontemplate is the child of eventsetup which is the parent of papertypologies.
cocus#Review_Form_Setup: reviewformsetup is a child of reviewform and eventsetup which is the parent of eventtracks.
cocus#Misc: helprequest is the child of helprequest and the parent of assistance.
cocus#Author: The author is the parent of the correspondingauthor and the child of the user. The administrator is the parent of the user.
cocus#Event_Creation: Eventcreation is a child of activity which is parented by registration.
cocus#Approval_Email: approvalemail is a child of email and the parent document of submission.
cocus#Rejection_Email: rejectionemail is a child of email and a document which is the parent of a submission.
cocus#Submission: The submission is a child of the document which is the parent of the review.
cocus#Template: The template is child of document which is child of Thing.
cocus#Feature_Request: The helprequest is a child of the eventapproval activity and the featurerequest.
cocus#Committee: The child of a committee is the child of a user.
cocus#Event_Tracks: eventtracks is a child of eventsetup which is the parent of researchtopic.
cocus#Request: The helprequest is the parent of the eventcreation activity and the helprequest is the child of the request.
cocus#Activity: The parent of the registration activity is the eventcreation activity, the parent of the eventapproval activity is the helprequest activity and the parent of the assistance request.
cocus#Head_Role: The headrole is the child of the adminrole.
cocus#Detail: The detail is child of Thing.
cocus#Corresponding_Author: The correspondingauthor is the child of the author and the user.
cocus#Reviewer_Role: The reviewerrolle is the child of the headroll and the parent of the reviewerrolle.
cocus#Event_Approval: The eventapproval is child of the activity which is parented by the registration.
cocus#Registration: The registration is child of the activity which is parented by the eventapproval.
cocus#Full_Paper: The fullpage is a child of paper which is the parent of the abstract.
cocus#Research_Topic: eventsetup is the parent of emailtemplate and is a research topic.
cocus#Conference: The conference is the parent of the symposium.
cocus#Assistance: helprequest is the child of helprequest and is the parent of featurerequest.
cocus#Email_Template: The emailtemplate is the child of eventsetup which is the parent of submissiontemplate.
